Q8: Margin of Error and Sample Size
Margin of Error (MoE): The range added/subtracted from the sample mean.

Formula:
MoE=Zâ‹…  ( Ïƒ/ (n)^1/2 )
Impact of sample size:

Larger n â†’ smaller MoE

Example:

Surveying 100 vs 1000 people: larger sample reduces uncertainty and gives more accurate results.

